# iOS Networking

Platform-specific networking for `apps/ios/`. See `docs/api-integrations.md` for API overview.

## Stack

URLSession, async/await, Codable. APIClient factory with base URL and API key per instance.

## Conventions

- Use URLSession async/await; no third-party HTTP client in v1.
- Prefer generic `APIClient` entry points (e.g. `request(_ endpoint)` for Decodable response types) for shared transport behavior.
- Model paths with endpoint enums/structs for type-safe routing.
- Map all API errors (`URLError`, HTTP 4xx/5xx, timeout, decoding/serialization) to `AppError` at the data layer.
- Use `CodingKeys` only when JSON keys differ from Swift property names.
- Per-instance base URL and API key; no shared global client.
- Self-signed certs: use a `URLSessionDelegate`-based server-trust flow when the instance configuration allows it.

